DAY-11 OF  REAL  TIME DEVOPS JOURNEY WITH KODEKLOUD



TASK:



The Nautilus application development team recently finished the beta version of one of their Java-based applications, which they are planning to deploy on one of the app servers in Stratos DC. After an internal team meeting, they have decided to use the tomcat application server. Based on the requirements mentioned below 



a. Install tomcat server on App Server 1. 

b. Configure it to run on port 8083. 

c. There is a ROOT.war file on Jump host at location /tmp. 



Deploy it on this tomcat server and make sure the webpage works directly on base URL i.e curl http://stapp01:8083 





STEP 1:

>>>>login to appserver ,upgraded the necessity things and  install the tomcat.



step 2: 

  checked the status of tomact

>> systemctl status tomcat.



found that tomcat is not active 



step 3:

  Enabled the tomcat config and restarted the tomcat.



step 4:



Configured to the desired port.

>>> sudo vi /usr/share/tomcat/conf/server.yml  (default path )



Find the line:

<Connector port="8080" protocol="HTTP/1.1"  

and  changed to desired port



<Connector port="8083" protocol="HTTP/1.1"



AND RESTART THE SERVER .



STEP 5:

Deploy the ROOT.war File in  tomcat server in appserver.



copied the Root.war from jumphost to appserver



>>>scp /tmp/ROOT.war tony@stapp01:/tmp/



move the copied to tomcat sever 



>>>sudo mv /tmp/ROOT.war /usr/share/tomcat/webapps/



finally ,



curl http://stapp01:8083



now, JAVA application is running.



